##Doctor in Huanggang tells the story of the quarantine zone: Take a nap in a hazmat suit and jump whenever there's movement

Wechat, boyangcongpeople

The function introduces, peels off the human shell, records the real sensible life. Presented by the in-depth Reporting Department of the Beijing News.

The first case in Huanggang was a driver delivering seafood to the South China Seafood Market in Wuhan. For business reasons, the driver stopped at the Huangzhou central vegetable market in Huanggang.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Staff at Huangzhou District's People's Hospital have encouraged themselves by pasting "go Huanggang" on the back of their protective suits. Photo courtesy of the respondents

Beijing News Reporters Liang Jingyi and Wang Feixiang

Editor | Xuan Hua proofread | Li Shihui

The text is about 4,875 words and takes about nine minutes to read

The weather has been fine the last few days, and the sun is shining brightly.

February 10th, lin Fang (not his real name) , a doctor at the Huangzhou District people's Hospital in Huanggang, Hubei Province, who had been quarantined and adjusted at home, received a message after leaving the front line: "I feel like I have recovered well! "! Thank you for every day you have spent with us during this period of time... I am so proud, warm and touched to have you among us today."

The information came from a newly discharged patient with pneumonia, who felt his efforts were worth it.

Huanggang is about 70 km from Wuhan and is half an hour away by an inter-city train. When the spotlight is on Wuhan, Huanggang, the province's second most populous city, is also suffering.

As Chen Shaomin, deputy mayor of Huanggang, said, because of the lack of knowledge, inadequate preparation, relatively poor medical conditions, late treatment, detection capacity is relatively lagging, Huanggang epidemic was very serious. As of 2400 hours on 11 February, a total of 2,398 cases of new crown pneumonia had been reported in Huanggang.

As a front-line doctor facing new coronavirus pneumonia, Lin has witnessed the development of the Huanggang epidemic since January 15. A reporter from the HSINKING newspaper spoke to her and listened to her stories and observations.

Do not want to have a patient to come, but to greet everyone with a smile

Peeling the onion: When did you first come into contact with new coronary pneumonia?

Lin Fang: I was originally a doctor of integrated Chinese and Western medicine. I was temporarily transferred to the Second Department of aspiration on January 15. The day before that, on January 13, the hospital had suddenly set up a second division, sending in a director and three doctors to begin treating suspected patients.

Just after the 15th, I was put on the afternoon shift. In one afternoon, admitted 8 new coronary pneumonia suspected patients, really too busy to come, had to ask the director to help. The next day I worked the night shift, and 10 more just like it. It got the attention of the hospital, and the Dean was all over it.

Peeling the onion: How do you and other health care workers work with an ever-increasing number of patients?

Lin Fang: it was quite hard at the beginning, working three shifts. I don't get much rest on the night shift. And the night shift was supposed to start at 5:00 the day before and leave at 8:00 the next morning. But because patients and their families were panicking and people were always asking questions, several of the night shifts ended after 1 p.m. the next day.

In the early morning of January 17, I was really tired, so I sent out a friend circle. "I was exhausted many times in this early morning. I prayed silently in my heart not to come again. ". Because in December 2019, we stayed up all night because of swine flu. When the swine flu has finally passed and the new coronary pneumonia has returned, we really don't want any more patients coming. But I was positive, and later encouraged myself to "greet the next and the next with a smile that requires no praise or judgment. We are the people we love most in ourselves. "

Peeling onions: How was the initial patient? What are the characteristics?

Lin Fang: I remember the first patient was a 59-year-old woman. Before coming to our hospital, she had been treated outside for more than ten days. She did not have a fever or cough, and her symptoms were shortness of breath and dyspnea. But when we did the C.T. , we found a cloud-like pattern on the lungs.

Later the patient condition is quite similar, mostly is a fever a few days not to drop, dry cough. A blood test revealed that they were different from ordinary bacterial infections, in which white blood cells are high. These people had low white blood cell counts, low lymphocyte, and belonged to the viral pneumonia. CT Scans are also different from the previous flu, double lower lung is cloud-like flocculent, rapid development in the short term.

As a doctor who has worked for more than 20 years, I felt something was wrong when SARS was on the front line again in 2003.

Peeling the onion: Did you realize it was new coronary pneumonia?

Lin Fang: When we first received these cases, huanggang's CDC has not been able to test for nucleic acids (Chen Shaomin, deputy mayor of Huanggang, told the media that Huanggang had no right to test for new crown pneumonia until January 19; from January 20 to 22, Hubei Province gave up the right to test, but Huanggang did not have a new crown test; the test was not available until January 23) , so none of these patients can be diagnosed, only suspected. But we know in our hearts that these cases are probably new cases of coronary pneumonia, which is contagious.

Later we heard that the first case in Huanggang was a driver in Huangzhou District who was delivering seafood to the South China Seafood Market in Wuhan. For business reasons, the driver stopped at the Huangzhou central vegetable market in Huanggang. It was a very crowded market, and a lot of people went to it, including my first case, a 59-year-old woman in Florida, who was reading near the central market, and went grocery shopping every day.

In the early morning of January 24, in the isolation ward of Longwangshan senior citizens'apartment, Lin Fang quietly took photos of his colleagues wearing protective clothing and resting on chairs. Photo courtesy of the respondents

Peeling an onion: what's different about this year's Spring Festival for you?

Lin Fang: In fact, around the 20th day of the 12th Lunar Month, the atmosphere in Huanggang is still very strong. The old people are walking on the road with big bags and small bags. They go to the market to buy fish and meat. On January 14, my son and I went to the vegetable market to buy vegetables and make meatballs. There were not many people wearing masks in the vegetable market.

But I have been very busy at that time, every day with patients, families, the voice is Hoarse. At that time, there were very few protective materials and protective clothing. Everyone wanted to save money. Almost everyone puts on a hazmat suit first thing in the morning, doesn't drink water, doesn't go to the bathroom for a day, and some older doctors wear diapers.

I spent New Year's Eve in the hospital, too. On New Year's Eve, many medical workers take instant noodles as their dinner. I had been wearing a mask and was feeling nauseous, so I found a room with a window and ate at the window. There's a breeze blowing in. It's a breath of fresh air.

Return to the scene of the SARS attack 17 years ago

Peeling the onion: when was new Huanggang announced the new crown pneumonia confirmed patients, suspected patients in the designated isolation hospital?

Lin Fang: On January 23, the Huanggang city government released the first batch of three designated hospitals for fever outpatient services, including the Central Huanggang Hospital, the City Hospital of Traditional Chinese medicine and our hospital. At that time, the Dabie Mountains Regional Medical Center had not yet been built, so the designated medical treatment institutions for suspected patients were set up in Huimin Hospital, City Infectious Disease Hospital, and Lung Wang Shan elderly apartment in Huangzhou District.

The suspected patients we encountered in the outpatient department of our hospital were transferred to the old people's apartment in Longwangshan, where the old people had been moved ahead of time. Longwangshan may have been chosen because it is farther and more remote from the city centre. It used to be the site of the People's Hospital in Huangzhou District and was the site of the 2003 SARS outbreak.

Peeling onion: What about the old people's apartment in Longwangshan?

Lin Fang: I and some medical staff moved to the isolation area of Longwangshan senior citizens'apartment on January 22. The decoration there is some years old, some mottled walls, some hospital bed guardrail can not be used. Moved in the first two days, a lot of people in the yard to help clean up, just a few boxes to change the lamp.

Senior housing is on four floors. The first floor houses the pharmacy, the Pricing Hall and the Security Staff; the fourth floor houses the medical staff; and the second and third floors house patients and have a total of 90 beds. Before the Dabie Mountains Regional Medical Center opened, we added a few extra beds in the hallway, which is about 100.

Peeling onions: What about the medical staff during quarantine?

Lin Fang: In the quarantine zone, we also worked very hard, but better than before. Sometimes you may fall asleep as soon as you sit down, and fall asleep while you eat. One day, shortly after 5:00 am, I took a photo of my shift-changing colleagues, all of them in their isolation suits, asleep in their chairs, unable to see who they were, and I called them "sleeping beauties. ".

Since the only way to get out of the suit is to go to the clean room, most people fall asleep in their chairs when they're tired. If something happens to a nearby patient, he can jump out of his chair like a Classical conditioning. Those chairs are comfortable, but the isolation clothing is very thin, the day is always walking do not feel, at night sit down to sleep will feel a bit cold.

Actually, nurses work harder than doctors, because family members are not allowed to stay in the ward, and patients are cared for by nurses. There is a critically ill patient, just changed a new sheet to urinate, the nurse changed a new sheet, but soon the patient and Shit, the nurse will clean again, change the sheets.

The nurses were young girls in their twenty, persistent and dedicated.

Shucking onions: in the days before and after Chinese New Year, new cases are confirmed daily in Huanggang, with dozens or even hundreds of new cases. Will 100 beds be enough?

Lin Fang: actually, I'm quite nervous.

I remember on January 24th a family of three, all suspected, the parents moved in, but the son has no bed. In order to let the child can also be hospitalized, the father and our doctor, the nurse quarrels, the mother unceasingly kowtows to us. The hospital wanted to help, so they put a cot in the middle of their parents'bed.

Peeling onions: What treatment will a suspected patient receive after admission?

Lin Fang: the first use of drugs, mainly some conventional antiviral drugs, plus some Lianhua Qingwen capsules such proprietary Chinese medicine. We have also used a drug for AIDS, because some research institutions believe that it may be effective against the new coronavirus. Some family members went to buy their own IMMUNOGLOBULIN, said there is no specific drug to increase immunity. Anyway, it was a time of planes and cannons, as long as the patient tolerated it.

But it's a lot better than it was, and on February 4th the fifth edition of the COVID-19 came out with much more detail about the routine. For example, it says you can try-interferon nebulizer inhalation, Lopinavir Ritonavir, Ribavirin Welling IV, etc. , in detail. You can pretty much do that now.

People who have experienced SARS should be more calm

PEELING ONION: Longwangshan elderly apartment bed tension, is from when it began to ease up?

Linfang: On January 23, the Huanggang CDC sent a team to Huangzhou District people's Hospital to take blood samples and throat swabs from the patients, after which nucleic acid tests were carried out. On Jan. 25, more than 50 of the 90 people were diagnosed, and after Jan. 28, the patients were transferred to the Dabie Mountains Regional Medical Center, where beds were less crowded.

Peeling the onion: Did you ever hear from any of the confirmed patients who were referred to the Dabie Mountains Regional Medical Center?

Lin Fang: Yes. One patient who was transferred to Dabie Mountains said that the Shandong medical team that he had supported in the past had been good and responsible, giving them great confidence that he would be released from the hospital soon. Because before there are patients'families worried that the patient will be discriminated against, I am afraid that he also has this worry, so tell him not to have any psychological pressure, to good physical exercise, timely calcium, young and strong are all good.

Peeling onions: The number of newly confirmed cases in Huanggang peaked around February 1 and 2, with 276 and 244 cases respectively, and remained around 100 after February 8, according to the Hubei Provincial Health Commission, on February 10th and 11th IT fell below 100. But on February 11th Liu Xuerong, Huanggang's Communist Party chief, said 13,000 people had been found to have fever. So, how are things in Huanggang these days?

Lin Fang: On the whole, the number of new cases in Huanggang has dropped. Confirmed patients have also been transferred to the Dabie Mountains Regional Medical Center, where we are supported by medical teams from Shandong and Hunan.

The fever screening actually started in January, when communities called House to house to see if anyone had a fever or cough, and then checked in, followed up with confirmed, suspected patients and their families, and I got calls myself. But phone calls can not urge patients to hospital treatment, or some people will go to the pharmacy to buy drugs, at home to eat.

But from February 10, Huanggang pharmacies will no longer be allowed to sell fever medicine, cough medicine, any symptoms must be to fever clinic screening. Such a move would certainly be good for the epidemic.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Volunteers helped rebuild the Dabie Mountains Regional Medical Center in Huanggang. It had just rained and the ground was muddy. Volunteers lifted the hospital bed and carried it into the building. Photo Beijing News App

Peeling the onion: What do you think of the future outbreak in Huanggang?

Lin Fang: these days, several of my patients have been discharged from the hospital. I think there will be fewer patients, because there will be more and more TV propaganda, more and more strict management in the community, and there will be no aggregated contact, so the possibility of infection will be much less.

I'm more concerned about the increase in the number of infected health care workers. Because there's a lot of risk in a general ward, because a patient with nausea, vomiting, acute gastroenteritis could be a probable or positive case. But protective clothing and other resources are priority support isolation ward, so the General Ward Staff is not easy to prevent.

I also have a number of health care workers infected, the current diagnosis of about four or five. Fortunately, the medical staff infection, found are still relatively timely, lung infection focus is relatively small, symptoms are not too serious, so everyone seems to be in good mood. Of course, there's always the possibility that you're nervous.

PEELING ONION: 17 years ago you experienced "SARS" , and now also experienced new coronary pneumonia, feel twice what is the difference?

Lin Fang: it must be different. In 2003, there was only one imported case in Huanggang during the SARS epidemic and the general practice was quarantined as soon as it was discovered. Back then, it was all about one person, and the average person saw it on television, and they didn't really learn a lot about pandemic disease.

This time the number of infected people, we have a direct feeling of the epidemic. In the quarantine zone, doctors and nurses take care of each other, reminding each other whose masks and gloves are not properly worn. The logistics staff was also very warm-hearted, because at that time moved to Longwangshan very hastily, a lot of supplies did not arrive, they help us all kinds of supplies are in place, including hand cream, slippers and other small things have.

Even My neighbors knew I was in quarantine, and they donated 1,000 goggles to our hospital. People say the neighbors in the city don't deal with each other very much, go their separate ways, but this time I feel very warm.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"Victory to the People's Hospital of Huangzhou District! ! ! ! " was posted on the back of the protective clothing by medical staff of the Huangzhou District People's Hospital

PEELING ONION: After this new pneumonia, have you thought about what you're going to do after the outbreak?

Lin Fang: For me, health is the first priority. For the medical staff, health is a responsibility.

In fact, as the first batch of people into the front line, I insisted half a month later, my heart will also be uneasy, worried about patients with serious illness, poor treatment, also afraid of fatigue under their own infection, but finally decided to cheer up. After all, I experienced the "SARS" battle, should be more relaxed than that year.

After the outbreak, I would like to get together with friends, because I am a lively person, hope to find a place where we can face to face to eat a big meal, sing songs, enjoy the noise.
